    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skin on) into thin chips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/festive-double-stacked-bacon-and-gravy-cheeseburger-with-sage-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and your <strong>dried sage</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15-20 min or until they are starting to brown \u2013 these are your <strong>festive fries</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/festive-double-stacked-bacon-and-gravy-cheeseburger-with-sage-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot over a medium heat with a knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk in your <strong>beef stock </strong>into the <strong>roux</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains \u2013 this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/festive-double-stacked-bacon-and-gravy-cheeseburger-with-sage-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chips and gravy are cooking, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>mince</strong> to a bowl, season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and roll into 2 meatballs per person</p><p>Once the chips are starting to brown, push them to one side of the tray[s], add your <strong>smoked streaky bacon </strong>to the other and return to the oven for 12-15 min or until the chips are crispy and the bacon is golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/festive-double-stacked-bacon-and-gravy-cheeseburger-with-sage-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong>, press them down firmly with a spatula to form a thin burger shape and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly charred on the bottom</p><p>Flip the <strong>burgers</strong> and top half with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and cook, covered, for 2-3 min further or until the burgers are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the cheese has melted</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use to 2 pans!) </p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/festive-double-stacked-bacon-and-gravy-cheeseburger-with-sage-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the burgers are cooking, cut the ends off your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> and slice in half</p><p>Tip: Don't chuck the crusts away. Instead, turn them into croutons!</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Add the<strong> ciabatta</strong> and <strong>brioche</strong> <strong>halves</strong> to a separate tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until toasted</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/festive-double-stacked-bacon-and-gravy-cheeseburger-with-sage-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once toasted, add the<strong> ciabatta</strong> to the <strong>gravy</strong> and set aside for 1-2 min or until it has started to soak up the gravy</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, pat it dry with kitchen paper and shred</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/festive-double-stacked-bacon-and-gravy-cheeseburger-with-sage-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>brioche base </strong>and<strong> lid</strong> with your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>cranberry sauce</strong></p><p>Top the <strong>brioche base</strong> with some<strong> shredded lettuce</strong>,<strong> </strong>the<strong> cheesy patty</strong>,<strong> gravy-soaked ciabatta</strong>, <strong>remaining patty</strong>, <strong>crispy bacon</strong>, more<strong> shredded lettuce </strong>and the <strong>brioche lid</strong></p><p><strong>Skewer</strong> the burger and serve the<strong> festive fries</strong> and any <strong>remaining gravy</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
